# File: specs/feature-add-address-pr-comments-skill-to-close-the-pr-review-loop/feature.gherkin
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-add-address-pr-comments-skill-to-close-the-pr-review-loop/requirements.md
# Issue: #86

Feature: /address-pr-comments skill
  As a developer using Claude Code or an automated SDLC runner
  I want a local slash-command skill that reads automated-reviewer threads on a PR, applies fixes via /write-code + /verify-code, and loops until review-clean
  So that PR review findings are resolved locally without manual intervention or switching to a cloud tool

  Background:
    Given a GitHub pull request exists on the current feature branch
    And the user has gh CLI authenticated with GITHUB_TOKEN
    And the project has steering documents at steering/ and this skill's bundle at skills/address-pr-comments/

  # --- Happy Path ---

  Scenario: AC1 — Entry preconditions validated on a clean PR
    Given the PR is open and the current branch matches the PR head ref
    And the working tree has no staged or unstaged changes
    When the user invokes /address-pr-comments
    Then the skill resolves the PR number from the branch
    And preconditions pass
    And the workflow proceeds to fetching threads

  Scenario: AC2 — Fetch unresolved review threads via GraphQL
    Given preconditions have passed
    When the skill queries reviewThreads(first:100) with comments(first:50)
    Then unresolved threads are returned
    And the result is filtered to threads whose author __typename is "Bot" or whose login matches the configured allow-list

  Scenario: AC3 — Short-circuit when PR is review-clean on entry
    Given no unresolved automated-reviewer threads exist
    And gh pr reviews returns no CHANGES_REQUESTED state
    When the skill finishes the initial fetch
    Then the skill prints "PR #N is review-clean — no action taken."
    And the skill exits with code zero
    And no sub-skills are invoked
    And no commits or pushes are made

  Scenario: AC4 — No automated reviewer has posted on the PR
    Given the PR exists but no review has been posted by the automated reviewer
    When the skill finishes the initial fetch
    Then the skill prints "No automated-reviewer threads found on PR #N — nothing to address."
    And the skill exits with code zero
    And the message is distinguishable from the AC3 "review-clean" message

  Scenario: AC5 — Classify each unresolved thread
    Given one or more unresolved automated-reviewer threads
    When the skill evaluates each thread
    Then each thread is classified as exactly one of clear-fix, ambiguous, or disagreement
    And each classification carries a one-sentence rationale retained for later reply and escalation messages

  Scenario: AC6 — Fix a clear-fix thread end-to-end via /write-code + /verify-code
    Given an unresolved clear-fix thread naming a specific file and line
    When the skill addresses the thread
    Then /write-code is invoked with the thread text, file path, line number, and diff hunk as context
    And /verify-code is invoked after /write-code completes
    And the fix is committed on the current branch with a "fix: address review finding on {file}:{line}" message

  Scenario: AC7 — Postcondition verification before replying
    Given /write-code and /verify-code have completed for a clear-fix thread
    When the skill evaluates whether to reply and resolve
    Then it confirms the commit SHA changed, the fix commit touches the referenced file, and /verify-code reported no regressions
    And if any postcondition fails, no reply is posted, the thread is not resolved, the thread joins the skipped-set, and the skill continues to the next thread

  Scenario: AC8 — Reply and resolve after a successful fix
    Given a clear-fix thread where all postconditions passed
    When the skill responds
    Then a reply is posted via gh api REST to POST /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{pull_number}/comments/{comment_id}/replies with a body naming the fix commit SHA
    And the thread is marked resolved via the GraphQL resolveReviewThread mutation

  # --- Alternative Paths ---

  Scenario: AC9 — Ambiguous or disagreement thread in interactive mode
    Given a thread classified as ambiguous or disagreement
    And the sentinel .claude/unattended-mode does not exist
    When the skill processes the thread
    Then AskUserQuestion is invoked with the thread text, classification, rationale, and three options: "Fix it anyway", "Skip — leave unresolved", "Reply without fixing"
    And the user's selection routes the thread to the matching outcome

  Scenario: AC10 — Ambiguous or disagreement thread in unattended mode
    Given a thread classified as ambiguous or disagreement
    And the sentinel .claude/unattended-mode exists
    When the skill processes the thread
    Then the skill prints "ESCALATION: address-pr-comments — pr=#N thread={id} classification={class} rationale={one-sentence}"
    And AskUserQuestion is not invoked
    And the thread joins the skipped-set and is left unresolved

  # --- Loop, Push, and Polling ---

  Scenario: AC11 — Push after each round uses plain git push
    Given one or more commits were produced in the current round
    When the round ends
    Then the skill runs plain "git push"
    And no --force, --force-with-lease, or --force-if-includes variant is ever passed
    And if the remote has diverged, the push is rejected, the skill prints the rejection, and exits non-zero without retry

  Scenario: AC12 — Loop until review-clean or round cap
    Given a round has finished processing all fetched threads and pushing
    When the loop re-evaluates
    Then the skill polls for the reviewer to re-run at 30-second intervals for up to 30 minutes
    And re-fetches unresolved threads, excluding any in the in-process skipped-set
    And exits with code zero when gh pr reviews shows no CHANGES_REQUESTED and the unresolved-minus-skipped set is empty
    And exits with a non-zero round-cap diagnostic when the configured max rounds (default 10) is reached without reaching review-clean

  Scenario: AC13 — Re-review polling timeout
    Given the skill has pushed fix commits and is polling for the reviewer to re-run
    When 30 minutes elapse with no new thread and no change in CHANGES_REQUESTED state
    Then the skill prints "Re-review polling timeout reached after 30 min on round {N} — exiting so you can investigate."
    And the skill exits non-zero
    And no threads are resolved and no commits are amended or reverted

  Scenario: AC14 — No force-push under any circumstance
    Given any push invocation inside the skill — per-round, retry, or final
    When the push command is built
    Then only "git push" is used
    And --force, --force-with-lease, and --force-if-includes are never passed
    And this holds in interactive mode, unattended mode, on push rejection, and regardless of any AskUserQuestion selection

  Scenario: AC15 — Unattended-mode livelock guard
    Given unattended mode is active
    And a round produced zero commits because every thread was escalated per AC10
    When the loop considers starting another round
    Then the skill exits with code zero
    And prints "Round {N}: {M} threads escalated, 0 fixes applied — exiting unattended loop."
    And no further rounds occur

  # --- Integration ---

  Scenario: AC16 — SDLC pipeline diagram reflects the new step
    Given the README and every SDLC skill show the pipeline diagram in their Integration section
    When this skill ships
    Then README.md's pipeline diagram contains "/address-pr-comments #N" immediately after "/open-pr #N"
    And every SDLC SKILL.md's "Integration with SDLC Workflow" chain that shows the full pipeline is updated to include the new step in the same position
